name: Loft View in San Mateo Family Home
space: Hello!  Thanks for looking at our listing!   Please read my description in its entirety to see if we have a potential fit. We  look forward to hosting guests of different backgrounds and welcome you to our sunny tranquil family home in San Mateo with a view of San Francisco Bay.  Our home is spacious and cozy, and is very kid friendly.  Our home is ideal for vacationers or those on business, and we will always make you feel at home.  We are in an ideal location, close to hwy 101 and 280, and public transportation.We are 20 miles south of San Francisco, 30 miles north of San Jose, 36 miles west of the Tri Valley and 13 miles from half Moon Bay and beaches.  We are 10-15 minutes from SFO.   If you must use public transportation, Sam Trans #53 passes close to here.  The Caltrain station is 1.5 miles away.  You can park there or walk there.  Keep in mind if you walk, it is a rigorous walk back up the hill.  The train is a 20 minute ride to SF.  I can send you a referral code for a free rid
description: Hello!  Thanks for looking at our listing!   Please read my description in its entirety to see if we have a potential fit. We  look forward to hosting guests of different backgrounds and welcome you to our sunny tranquil family home in San Mateo with a view of San Francisco Bay.  Our home is spacious and cozy, and is very kid friendly.  Our home is ideal for vacationers or those on business, and we will always make you feel at home.  We are in an ideal location, close to hwy 101 and 280, and public transportation.We are 20 miles south of San Francisco, 30 miles north of San Jose, 36 miles west of the Tri Valley and 13 miles from half Moon Bay and beaches.  We are 10-15 minutes from SFO.   If you must use public transportation, Sam Trans #53 passes close to here.  The Caltrain station is 1.5 miles away.  You can park there or walk there.  Keep in mind if you walk, it is a rigorous walk back up the hill.  The train is a 20 minute ride to SF.  I can send you a referral code for a free rid
neighborhood_overview: The view from our home of the bay, San Mateo bridge, and Mt. Diablo is fabulous!  We live in an ideal location:  20-30 minutes from San Francisco, the East Bay, the South Bay (Silicon Valley), and the beach tom the west!  We are also a stroll away from a quarter mile hike to the highest peak on the peninsula with 180 degree view of the Bay Area.  We live down the street from the College of San Mateo, which has a state-of-the-art gym.  A gourmet grocery store, drugstore, and many eateries are a 5-10 minute walk away.
notes: We kindly ask our guests to participate with us in our eco-conscious efforts by recycling, composting, and being mindful of the environment. Please turn off lights not in use, and during daylight.  Please turn off air conditioner, fan, or heaters when not in use, and at night while sleeping.
transit: The Caltrain station is 1  1/2 miles from us.  It is an easy walk down and a rigorous walk UP the hill (that's why we have a great view!).  We have parking on our street and driveway.  Please be mindful of where you park and do not block my neighbors' driveways.  A cab, Uber, or Lyft is the best way to get here from the airport, which is 10 miles away.  If it is your first time using Uber or Lyft, I can send you a referral code for a free first ride.
access: Free WiFi. Kitchen:  Guests will have access to the kitchen for light cooking.  There is shelf space for dry goods and a mini fridge dedicated to guests, which you would share with other guests (there is a limit to the quantity of food to store in the refrigerator and shelves, so please be mindful of this).   Also, while we are vegetarians ourselves, we are open and happy to accommodate our meat-eating guests for occasional meat-cooking.  However, frequent meat cookers would find a better fit elsewhere. Guests who are staying for 1 week minimum have access to laundry at no extra charge.  I do require that you ask me for instructions prior to use, and laundry is limited to 2 loads/week per party.
interaction: We love hosting our guests and getting to know them.  We also respect those guests who don't have the time to chat or hang out!
house_rules: This is a very quiet residential neighborhood.  My neighbors are super awesome and we love and respect them!  Please be courteous to and considerate of them.  No blocking driveways, and no loud noise or disruptions after 10pm.  If you are enjoying the stars in any of the outdoor spaces, please keep the talking level low after 10pm. Non-smokers only and no smoking on property.  This is a family kid-friendly home, so plan accordingly. Additional guests that are not part of original booking are not allowed.  Respectful and considerate travelers who clean up after themselves are welcome! Children of any age do count as additional guests.  For security purposes, I will photocopy all guests' IDs upon arrival. Please, no shoes worn in the home and no food & drinks outside of the kitchen and dining room.  No perfumes as I am allergic! Extra fees will incur for:  Leaving a large amount of belongings to be disposed, or cooking which results in strong-smelling odors (which require extra cleaning)
host_about:
We are a homeschooling family and are bilingual in English and Italian.  We are passionate about too many things to list!  On the top of our list are cooking, gardening, art, animals, travel, world music, cultural diversity, etc, etc, etc!!!  We also love expanding our understanding of the world by meeting people of diverse backgrounds.
We have a deep love for the region we live in and feel confident in recommending places to go in the Bay area.  We look forward to be a part of your wonderful stay in our part of the world!

name: Snug & Cozy Queen Room w/Parking & BRFT!
summary: Snug & cozy room is available at our vintage inspired home in downtown Burlingame. It's has a garden view, with a shared bathroom  claw foot tub. Parking too.Registered guests only in the home. Kindly keep voice down while visiting our home to be respectful of our other guests. Your rental is for your room/use of restrooms, and breakfast nook for light breakfast served from 8-9:30AM. The rest of our home is our use only.  No children please. Sorry, cooking privileges not allowed, mircowave only.
space: This 110 year old home in downtown Burlingame is lovingly styled, fully furnished with 'Anthropologie' style furnishings, on almost a 1/2 acre and walking distance to a trendy avenue where you'll find Starbucks to Banana Republic to wonderful ethnic restaurants and amazing shopping!  This bedroom is set for 2 guests only w/ a queen bed & shared restroom upstairs & a 1/2 bath downstairs. *As much as we love pets, please inquire as to charges $25. Per day, per pet and our requirements, we will consider your pet on further discussion with guest. Thanks for understanding:). No children under 12 please. Thank you. Lisa

neighborhood_overview: We love that so much is available within walking distance, including our beautiful library, .'Burlingame Avenue' which has been recently beatified with lovely European style sidewalks, cafes, boutiques and wonderful restaurants.
notes: Free parking available on property while you are booked at home. If you arrive after 10:00 PM, the front door is locked. Please come in through the back gate off the deck. I will send information on the house once the room is booked.  Please read our terms of use of our home.  Also note, this is a perfume free home.  No children under 12 please. Thank you, Lisa
transit: CalTrain is a mere 2 block walk to ride either to San Francisco or to San Jose. BART heads North to San Francisco or the East Bay and SFO. Airport is a 10 minute drive from our home. Uber or Lyft services available.
access: Easy access to our home, upstairs bedroom. A Home-made breakfast with freshly brewed coffee, tea, house-made muffins, fresh fruit, yogurt is included. Weekday breakfast is scheduled 8:00 AM, 8:30-9:30 weekends. Microwave may be utilized,  kitchen not available for cooking. The rental includes the bedroom/bathrooms. Others rooms in home are for use for my family only. Laundry not available. Laundromat in town. Thank you.
interaction: We live at premises, along with our Dog. However, we offer privacy and respect to our guests. Please remember we may have other guests onsite, indoor voices please:).
house_rules: The golden rule! Please treat our home as your home! Please be considerate of neighbors, no parties please! Cleanliness is next to Godliness! We are excited to make our home available to folks whom share the same views as us:) Quiet Time: 10PM-9AM Have fun, enjoy!
host_about: I love to entertain, it's how I have made a living for the last couple of decades. Our home is very relaxed, easy going & busy too! I love all that family involves; laughter of kids, warm smells of housebaked desserts, animals underfoot & about, wonderful conversation & of course, quiet time with a book that's been calling my name, for ahem, months to read:).

name: HackerHome - Millbrae Caltrain 2
summary: The HackerHome Network Whether you're new to the Valley, bored with your current housing or need a transient place... I would like to help. When you reserve with me, you'll have instant friends and be part of a network of 10+ homes in the Bay Area.
space: Newly remodeled home with an open kitchen, living room and a huge backyard for BBQs.
description: The HackerHome Network Whether you're new to the Valley, bored with your current housing or need a transient place... I would like to help. When you reserve with me, you'll have instant friends and be part of a network of 10+ homes in the Bay Area. Newly remodeled home with an open kitchen, living room and a huge backyard for BBQs. All utilities are included and free WIFI. Clean linens/bedding, pillow and blanket are provided. Why would someone say light cooking?  Home prepped meals really warms up the house and it's encouraged. It's a house full of people & different schedules.  So please use ear plugs if necessary.  If you're a light sleeper or can't sleep on a single mattress, this may not be the right place for you.  We are a very communal/respectful group and strive to provide space for everyone to work and hangout.  Remember that work, musical instruments and books take precedence over the television. This is downtown Millbrae!  It's a super convenient location and only a half mi
neighborhood_overview: This is downtown Millbrae!  It's a super convenient location and only a half mile (or a 10 minute walk) to Millbrae Bart and Caltrain Station.   You're also only 1 block to downtown Millbrae where many restaurants close late, kinkos business center, UPS store, Peet's coffee, Safeway grocery store and many restaurants.
notes: More than one suitcase? Consult with me prior to making your reservation. Respectful Housing for Women Females in a separate room. If you'd like to stay in the girls' room, please check with me on availability before reserving.  If you don't have a preference, then just make your reservation. Cleaning The Airbnb cleaning fee is to make sure you have a clean bed upon arrival and not to clean up after you. All spaces are shared, so please be mindful of picking up after yourself.   Best Way to Reach Me 1. Complete your Airbnb profile with an ID/Passport and connect your social networks.  2. One line about your purpose of visit.  3. Let me know your estimated time of arrival.
transit: Walk 10 minutes to Millbrae Caltrain and Bart Station. This house is less than 3km from SFO.  Take an Uber and you'll be here in less than 10 minutes from the San Francisco Airport.
access: All utilities are included and free WIFI. Clean linens/bedding, pillow and blanket are provided. Why would someone say light cooking?  Home prepped meals really warms up the house and it's encouraged.
interaction: It's a house full of people & different schedules.  So please use ear plugs if necessary.  If you're a light sleeper or can't sleep on a single mattress, this may not be the right place for you.  We are a very communal/respectful group and strive to provide space for everyone to work and hangout.  Remember that work, musical instruments and books take precedence over the television.
house_rules: Clean your dishes right away If you must invite an associate/friend over, consult with me first Be conscientious of morning bathroom usage Do not snooze your alarm Use earphones, not speakers - unless it's a family event We Prefer That You be respectful of the space and to fellow housemates clean up after yourself by making your bed and washing your dishes have an optimistic outlook and laugh a lot =D

name: HackerHome - Menlo Park: bunk 4
summary: The HackerHome Network Whether you're new to the Valley, bored with your current housing or need a transient place... I would like to help. When you reserve with me, you'll have instant friends and be part of a network of 10+ homes in the Bay Area.
space: Spacious ranch style home with a U-shape floor plan with communal spaces in the front and sleeping quarters in the back 3 bedrooms - no private rooms at this location  4 full bathrooms  3+ work areas - communal and private work spaces! The females have a bathroom just for themselves.
description: The HackerHome Network Whether you're new to the Valley, bored with your current housing or need a transient place... I would like to help. When you reserve with me, you'll have instant friends and be part of a network of 10+ homes in the Bay Area. Spacious ranch style home with a U-shape floor plan with communal spaces in the front and sleeping quarters in the back 3 bedrooms - no private rooms at this location  4 full bathrooms  3+ work areas - communal and private work spaces! The females have a bathroom just for themselves. All utilities are included and free WIFI. Clean linens/bedding, pillow and blanket are provided. Why would someone say light cooking?  Home prepped meals really warms up the house and it's encouraged. It's a house full of people & different schedules.  So please use ear plugs if necessary.  If you're a light sleeper or can't sleep on a single mattress, this may not be the right place for you.  We are a very communal/respectful group and strive to provide space f
neighborhood_overview: Located in the heart of Menlo Park and just a 5 minute walk to Menlo Park Caltrain Station, restaurants and groceries. Downtown Palo Alto and Stanford are also really accessible from the home. Nealon Park and Burgess Park are super close. The Guild Theatre hosts midnight screenings of the Rocky Horror Shows on the first Saturday of every month. Café Borrone has an excellent menu and atmosphere. Downtown Menlo is stacked with good eats and great grocers like Trader Joe's and Draeger's.  Other establishments that are less than a block away include: Safeway, Starbucks, CVS & BevMo.  Palo Alto: You are less than half a mile from Stanford Mall and only one mile away from downtown Palo Alto! Stanford University and Palo Alto Town & Country Plaza is just an arm’s reach away from there.
notes: More than one suitcase? Consult with me prior to making your reservation. Respectful Housing for Women Females in a separate room. If you'd like to stay in the girls' room, please check with me on availability before reserving.  If you don't have a preference, then just make your reservation. Cleaning The Airbnb cleaning fee is to make sure you have a clean bed upon arrival and not to clean up after you. All spaces are shared, so please be mindful of picking up after yourself.   Best Way to Reach Me 1. Complete your Airbnb profile with an ID/Passport and connect your social networks.  2. One line about your purpose of visit.  3. Let me know your estimated time of arrival.
transit: The location is ideal in terms of walkability. Caltrain is conveniently located on the other side of El Camino Real.
access: All utilities are included and free WIFI. Clean linens/bedding, pillow and blanket are provided. Why would someone say light cooking?  Home prepped meals really warms up the house and it's encouraged.
interaction: It's a house full of people & different schedules.  So please use ear plugs if necessary.  If you're a light sleeper or can't sleep on a single mattress, this may not be the right place for you.  We are a very communal/respectful group and strive to provide space for everyone to work and hangout.  Remember that work, musical instruments and books take precedence over the television.
house_rules: Clean your dishes right away If you must invite an associate/friend over, consult with me first Be conscientious of morning bathroom usage Do not snooze your alarm Use earphones, not speakers - unless it's a family event We Prefer That You be respectful of the space and to fellow housemates clean up after yourself by making your bed and washing your dishes have an optimistic outlook and laugh a lot =D
